    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-04-12T04:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1954-04-12T04:00:00-05:00" n="792"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d792">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">884A.86/4–1254: Telegram</note>
                <head>No. 792<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Department of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d792fn1">Repeated to Tel Aviv and Paris.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">priority</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1954-04-12T10:00:00+01:00"
                            >April 12, 1954—10 a.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>4489. I mentioned to <persName corresp="#p_ESA1">Eden</persName> last evening
                        <persName corresp="#p_CWS1">Churchill</persName>’s message to <persName
                        corresp="#p_SM2">Sharett</persName> (<gloss target="#t_Deptel1"
                        >Deptel</gloss> 5344 to London)<note n="2" xml:id="d792fn2">
                        <ref target="#d789">Document 789</ref>.</note> and discussed possibility of
                    my sending similar message. <persName corresp="#p_ESA1">Eden</persName> unaware
                    UK Embassy instructed to tell us about <persName corresp="#p_CWS1"
                        >Churchill</persName>’s message. He said that since <persName
                        corresp="#p_CWS1">Churchill</persName> considered pro-Zionist a message from
                    him had seemed desirable but doubted desirability of supporting message from
                    US.</p>
                <p>In view of above and fact that further message from me might be construed as
                    resulting from my visit London rather than from our own initiative do not
                    believe we should send any message at this time.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>[<persName corresp="#p_DJF2">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Dulles</hi>
                        </persName>]</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
